    <briefdescription>
<para>AArch64 lower-EL trap frame used for syscall/fork handoff. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The FP/SIMD block is appended after the general-purpose fields so their offsets (hardcoded in boot.S) stay stable: q[] at +288, fpsr +800, fpcr +808, total 816 bytes. User processes may use FP/NEON (ports such as ncurses do); kernel code is -mgeneral-regs-only, so the exception paths in boot.S are the only place this state is saved and restored. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
